<h2 id="how-pixltonian-works" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#how-pixltonian-works" aria-hidden="true">#</a> How Pixltonian works?</h2>
<p>Under the Pixltonian system, users own and have control over their own files through public-key cryptography, and the applications can only use rather than control users' files. For a more detailed description you can read <a href="https://Pixltonian.notion.site/3-Platformless-Media-55505c45a49743a2b89304abcb4a90da" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Platformless Media<ExternalLinkIcon/></a></p>
<p>Pixltonian Protocol defines the format of information presence and communication, and through the protocol, users store signed information to decentralised Pixltonian Network, including profile, link, note and asset, where note and asset include not only signed content published by users themselves, but also content automatically indexed from other networks. Details of the Pixltonian Protocol can be found <a href="/protocol.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>.</p>
<p>The Pixltonian Protocol is designed to be very flexible, and using the Pixltonian Protocol and Pixltonian Network, you can do many types of applications, two typical representatives are user profile applications and information flow applications, you can see our two demo applications <a href="https://cheers.bio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cheers<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> and <a href="https://revery.so/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Revery<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>. But we also do not limit and cannot predict what applications you will build.</p>
<p>With a basic understanding of the protocol, the quickest way to develop an Pixltonian application is to use the <a href="/sdk.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Pixltonian SDK<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>, or to request <a href="/api.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">API<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> directly.</p>
<p>Reading <a href="https://Pixltonian.io/#/whitepaper" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">our white paper<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> is also a good way to learn more about the protocol and the upcoming decentralized Pixltonian Network.</p>
<p><img src="@source/images/system.png" alt="Pixltonian System"></p>
<p>If you have any questions, you can find us on <a href="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://discord.gg/Pixltonian" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> <a href="https://t.me/Pixltonian_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Telegram<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/Pixltonian_" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>. We'll be happy to help!</p>
<p>Pixltonian and its affiliated network are open and permissionless - If you are using Pixltonian for your project, we would be delighted if you <a href="https://github.com/NaturalSelectionLabs/Pixltonian/issues/21" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">let us know<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>. We will provide technical or operational assistance if you need it.</p>
